Title: Two-Part November IKKS Installment with EJ Kwandibens
Speaker: EJ Kwandibens
Topics: Eagle Staff Teachings, Preservation of Indigenous culture and wisdom, Belonging, Acceptance, Societal norms, Healing (personal and community level)
Dates: Nov. 21, 12:00pm – 1:30pm (ET) and Nov. 30, 12:00pm – 1:30pm (ET)
Location: George Brown College
Goals: Increase awareness of Indigenous culture among students and staff, Host events, workshops, social gatherings to share cultural knowledge
Indigenous Counselor: Laraine Hale

Website Links: Check out past events, Learn more about our land acknowledgment, Sign Up Now
